Class Equipment

java.lang.Object
com.prototype.model.entities.Equipment
Direct Known Subclasses:
BiomedicalEquipment, TechEquipment
@Entity public abstract class Equipment extends Object
Base abstract entity that represents a generic equipment unit managed by the system. This class provides the shared structure and attributes for all equipment types (e.g., technological, medical, biomedical), while allowing specialized subclasses to extend it.

The inheritance strategy is JOINED, meaning each subclass has its own table while the common attributes remain in the equipments table.

This entity includes general descriptive information such as serial number, brand, model, classification type, operational status, the stored image reference, and the provider associated with the equipment.

      brand - manufacturer or brand
      model - model name
      type - general classification of the equipment
      state - operational status
      imagePath - reference to the stored image
      provider - supplier associated with the equipment
